title: Home
cleaned_text: Leonardo Franzese grew up in New Jersey and moved to Camano Island, Washington in 1995. The unmatched natural beauty of the mountains, Puget Sound, and forests have kept him firmly seated in the Pacific Northwest. Living in this area has fostered great interests in cooking, culture, hiking, biking, and hunting wild mushrooms to further his culinary pursuits. Dr. Franzese earned his doctorate in Naturopathic Medicine from Bastyr University. His interests are in primary care and physical medicine as it relates to chronic pain. Dr. Lenny also takes massage appointments as he is a licensed massage practitioner, and incorporates a number of other physical medicine modalities during his massage treatments to maximize the therapeutic effect.
